## Application Workflow

This web application evaluates a loan applicant’s credit risk using machine learning, business rules, explainable AI, and an interactive chatbot.

---

## Inputs

### User Inputs (via Web Interface)

The user provides the following details:

- Age  
- Monthly Income  
- Debt Ratio  
- Revolving Credit Utilization  
- Number of Open Credit Lines and Loans  
- Number of Real Estate Loans  
- Number of Dependents  
- Payment History (30–59, 60–89, and 90+ days past due)

### Automatically Derived Inputs

The system calculates additional features internally:

- Debt-to-Income Ratio  
- Age-to-Credit Ratio  

### Optional Inputs

- Identity proof upload  
- Income proof upload  

---

## Processing Steps

- Validate user input data  
- Convert inputs into model features  
- Scale features using a pre-trained scaler  
- Predict default risk using XGBoost  
- Adjust risk using business rules  
- Generate explanations using SHAP  
- Classify applicant risk level  

---

## Outputs

The application produces the following outputs:

- Base machine learning risk probability  
- Final adjusted risk score  
- Risk category (Low Risk / High Risk)  
- Loan decision (Approved / Rejected)  
- Feature-based risk explanation  

All outputs are displayed on the Streamlit dashboard.

---

## Virtual Loan Assistant (Chatbot)

The application includes an AI-powered chatbot that:

- Explains loan approval or rejection decisions  
- Suggests actions to reduce credit risk  
- Answers what-if questions related to applicant data  

This improves user interaction and understanding of the results.

---

## Data Persistence

The system stores:

- Applicant input information  
- Uploaded document metadata  
- Risk scores and final decisions  

This enables tracking, auditing, and review of previous assessments.
